         <abstract>
            <p>The cash budget requires sound forecasts of cash inflows and outflows for a specified period of time. To develop a cash inflow forecast, it is usually necessary to estimate the cash collection and bad debt expense rates to be applied to either credit sales or accounts receivable balances. The objective of this paper is to empirically estimate cash collection rates (payment proportions) and bad debt rates, via the lagged regression approach, relating cash collections and credit sales of prior periods.</p>
         </abstract>
